# AquaSense - HackOrbit Aqua Sync 🚀💧

AquaSense is an end-to-end water quality monitoring and analysis system built for HackOrbit 2025. It combines IoT-based data collection, a backend API, and a machine learning model for predictive analysis, with a clean React-based frontend dashboard.

## 📝 Table of Contents
- [Features](#features)
- [Tech Stack](#tech-stack)
- [Project Structure](#project-structure)
- [Setup & Installation](#setup--installation)
- [Usage](#usage)
- [Demo](#demo)
- [Contributors](#contributors)
- [License](#license)

## ✨ Features
✅ Real-time water quality monitoring  
✅ ML-based water potability prediction  
✅ Interactive and responsive React dashboard  
✅ RESTful API backend (Node.js + Express + MongoDB)  
✅ ML model served via FastAPI  
✅ Deployed on Render and Vercel for seamless access

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

### Frontend
- React.js
- Tailwind CSS
- Axios

### Backend
- Node.js
- Express.js
- MongoDB (Mongoose)

### Machine Learning
- Python
- FastAPI
- scikit-learn
- pandas

### Deployment
- Frontend: Vercel
- Backend API: Render
- ML API: Render

## 📁 Project Structure

HackOrbit-Aqua-Sync/
├── aquasense-frontend/ # React frontend
├── aquasense-backend/ # Node.js + Express backend API
└── aquasense-ml/ # FastAPI ML model deployment

